args:
So, um, Galkin has barricaded himself in
an abandoned village in the mountains
and begun...making demands to the
new government.
He says he wants power restored to him,\nand if his demands are not met, he'll use\nhis Brume to...cover the area in mist.
If he releases the mist up there, the\nmountain currents will carry it across\nthe entire nation.
He's essentially using the people of\nSvenitla as hostages.
He's willing to kill EVERYONE in Svenitla?!\nIs he out of his damn mind?!
To think a man sworn to protect his people\nmight turn his weapons against them...
Naturally, the government has no intention\nof complying with these demands.

However, the village they've set as their
base is surrounded by steep mountains,
and the only way in or out is by a single
road that connects to town.
That road is easily defended. No matter the\nnumbers we throw at them, they'll see us\ncoming and have the advantage.
So is there nothing we can do?
(We need another wayâ€”one that doesn't\ninvolve the mountains or the road...)
Hey, you took your antitoxin, yeah?

'Course I did! 'Cause if this deal goes
south, we're all set to use that Brume
right away. ...Huh? Wait, what the hell's
that?
...Wait. You want to attack from the SKY?!
It is the last thing they will expect.\nI will shapeshift and attack the village\nfrom above.
B-but the former king controls dangerous\nfiends as well as soldiers! It's too much\nfor one person to take on alone!
I am fully aware of the danger, but this is\nthe only way to stop his mad scheme.
And even if the plan were to fail,\nI would be the only loss.
(My foes have split into three groups.)
(One has come to face me, one is rushing\nto the church, and the last is fortifying\ntheir defenses in the main square.)

(The Brume is useless for their purposes
indoors, so those going to the church are
likely doing so in order to guard Galkin.
Which means...)
The enemy is heading for the square!\nHe's after the Brume!
There it is. Now to destroy it and... Fie!
This fiend is powerful indeed... Gah!

(I must still be weak from the wounds I
sustained in the mine; I don't think I'll be
able to hold this form much longer.
I'll need to take another approach...)
I'm delighted to see you prostrate yourself\nbefore me once more, Valyx.
If he's here, they ain't got no intention of\nmeeting our demands. Want me to\ndeploy the Brume, Yer Majesty?
Fool! Why would we do that when we now\nhave an Alberian prince for a hostage?
If we play our cards right, those pretenders\nwho sit upon my throne will have no\nchoice but to give us everything we want.
My people are a valuable tax base,\nafter all, so I'd prefer not to slaughter\nthem wholesale if I don't have to.

So you really do just see them as
commodities to be used for your own 
benefit... You are a disgusting excuse
for royalty, fallen or no!
Yet I am this country's rightful king!\nThe blood running through my veins\nserves as proof of this.
It is your blood lineage that makes you\nworthy of being a king in Alberia as well,\nis it not?
No. There are three traits of royalty.\nThe first is that you must be a person\nborn of a true and rightful bloodline.
But dragonblood is a power meant to\nprotect the people, and merely inheriting\nit does not make one a true regent.

They must be strong of body and heart to
utilize this powerâ€”this is the second trait.
And finally, they must have the faith of the
people to hold the country together.
Well, thank you for enlightening me.\nYet can you really, truly claim to possess\nALL of those qualities?

Of course, you have the blood of royalty
running through your veins, and your
coming here alone proves the mettle of
your body and heart...

But the faith of the people? I think not!
Why, they'd have to be mad to follow one
who served as a general for the heinous
Dyrenell Empire!
I once believed that none would follow\nme as I am now, and it would only be\nnatural for them not to accept me.
And even if the plan were to fail,\nI would be the only loss.
You are SUCH an idiot sometimes!

If you think we're just going to let you
waltz out of here just because YOU'LL be
the only loss, you're denser than the
handle of your own axe!
In a perilous situation like this,\nwe must accompany you.
You were forced to bear the burden\nof the imperial army's actions alone.
But you are now a general of Alberia.\nAnd as we are serving under you, you must\ntrust us to have your back.
I do not know what to say...
A country can't function without trust\nbetween a ruler and their people.
Your job isn't just to protect usâ€”it's to\nalso believe in us and count on us when\nthe chips are down.
I never thought the day would come when\nYOU would tell me how a ruler should be.
Still, how will the rest of you\ninfiltrate the village?
If you're going to shapeshift and come at\nthem from the skies, I have an idea...
We're nearing the drop-off point.\nIs your parachute ready?
Ready and able. I'll touch down just\noutside the village and await your signal.
...Even if you weren't directly responsible,\nI still find myself unable to forgive you for\nthe deaths of my subordinates.
And once this operation is over, I'm going\nto punch you as hard as I can in the face.\nSo don't you dare die before then.
I shall prepare my cheek for its inevitable\nbruising and pray for your safe return.

Victor wasn't the only one who grounded
nearbyâ€”and as I did battle with the fiend
in the square, I gave them the signal.
They must be arriving right about...now.
The signal went off here in the square,\nwhich means...
Let us put an end to it. Haaaah!
That takes care of the guards on the road!
Now the Svenitlan army can march in.
You have my thanks for your cooperation.\nNow to put an end to the former king.
We've finished encircling the village,\nCommander. Should we initiate an\nall-out attack?
Show the enemy a hell deeper than any\ndemon has yet knownâ€”and may the hell\nyou show our former ruler be deeper yet.

Noelle, relay a message to the enemies
who have barricaded themselves in.
If they surrender now, we will grant them
all a full pardon.
Our soldiers are surrenderin' before\nthey've even put up a fight!
The Brume's gone and a whole army's\nattackin'. There's no way we're winning\nthis. I'm outta here!
You utter imbeciles! You'll pay for\nthrowing your king to the wolves!
It is only natural that soldiers who fight\nmerely to sate their own greed would\nabandon you at the slightest misstep.
Perhaps if you had not abandoned your\npeople when the demon attacked,\nthis might have turned out differently.
No... It doesn't end here... I'm a king,\ndamn you! A king! A KIIIIIING!
Such desperate flailing embarrasses us\nboth. Do not humiliate yourself further.
Now go ruminate in a cell about what it\nTRULY takes to be a ruler.
